<br>
Lets say a quest was put in that allowed you to cave in Nagefens Liar.  Once done, Nagafen would be killed for ever.  No more Naggy raids.<br>
<br>
This is almost exactly like waking the Sleeper, except waking the Sleeper is worse.<br>
<br>
So now with Nagafen gone, you have to kill Ragefire, Tallendor, Malefin, (I really don't know all the dragons...), etc etc ... the same things you were looking for from Nagafen still exist on other red dragons.<br>
<br>
What has changed?  Instead of requiring 24 level 50 people to kill Naggy, you recquire a lot more levels or a lot more people.  So to get the same reward, it takes more people.<br>
<br>
This is why killing the Sleeper is worse.  At least you have the chance for the same reward.  Kill the Sleeper, and now it takes a lot more people for less reward.<br>
<br>
The part that would suck the most is that the people aren't caving in Naggys liar because they want to do a service and slay the giant red beast for ever ... but because they want to deny you Naggy.<br>
